      "note_no": "45",
      "note": "Lit., \"whereas God was more worthy (ahaqq) that thou shouldst stand in awe of Him\". Referring to this divine reprimand (which, in itself, disproves the allegation that the Qur'an was \"composed by Muhammad\"), A'ishah is reliably quoted as having said, \"Had the Apostle of God been inclined to suppress anything of what was revealed to him, he would surely have suppressed this verse\" (Bukhari and Muslim)."
